<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-27T05:25:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-27T05:25:00-05:00" n="645" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d645">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">884.6461 Tsana Dam/264:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ethiopia (<persName type="from">Southard</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-27T13:00:00+02:35">April
                                        27, 1931—1 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received April 27—2 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>8. The Emperor invites representatives of the White Corporation to
                                arrive here end of November for presentation and discussion Tsana
                                survey report. The British will be invited when they ask Ethiopian
                                Foreign Office and I have intimated such to the local British
                                Legation which is telegraphing London for authorization to proceed
                                accordingly.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Southard</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>